A man died after his motorbike crashed into a car on the R59 crossing over the N1 highway in Sasolburg, in the Free State, paramedics said on Sunday. When ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene, they found a light motor vehicle and wrecked motorbike lying in the middle of the road. The body of a man was found lying a few feet away from his motorcycle, he said. The man was immediately assessed by ER24 paramedics and found to have sustained numerous, fatal injuries and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done be done for the man and he was declared dead on the scene. He said there were no other injuries. The cause of the accident was not known and would be investigated. African News Agency (ANA)